<div class="description">
    <h3>Description</h3>

    <div class="body">
        <p>I have an XML-RPC server (also Zend Framework). The server has a method declared as :</p>

<pre class="highlight"><code> 
/**
 * @param integer|array $ids
 * @param string $language
 * @return struct
 */
public function get($ids, $language=null)
</code></pre>

<p>When I call that method (using the Zend_Xmlrpc_Client) as :</p>

<pre class="highlight"><code> 
$client-&gt;call('get', array(1));
</code></pre>

<p>The parameter is sent as array(1) instead of (int)1.</p>

<p>The parameter is sent correct when using :</p>

<pre class="highlight"><code>
$client-&gt;setSkipSystemLookup(true);
</code></pre>

